# Standard Operating Procedures

# {.tabset}

## DEL

#### IFR

| SID | SID Type | Pronounciation | Aircraft | Runways | Climb |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| EEVAA# | RNAV | eevaa | Jet | 17L/R 29, 35L/R | 13000 |
| GTGON# | RNAV | gtgon | Jet | 17L/R 29, 35L/R | 13000 |
| HIDEY# | RNAV | hidey | Jet | 17L/R 29, 35L/R | 13000 |
| LLIZY# | RNAV | llizy | Jet | 17L/R 29, 35L/R | 13000 |
| LOKRD# | RNAV | lokrd | Jet | 17L/R 29, 35L/R | 13000 |
| RDHSE# | RNAV | rdhse | Jet | 17L/R 29, 35L/R | 13000 |
| SPILR# | RNAV | spilr | Jet | 17L/R 29, 35L/R | 13000 |

**IFR (RNAV SID) Example**  
Cleared to Miami Intl airport via the LOKRD1 departure, then as filed. Maintain 13000, expect FL300 10 minutes after departure. Departure frequency 132.075, squawk 1234.

**IFR squawk code assignment:**  
via Aurora

#### Pre-Departure Clearance
[PDC](/pdc) via CPDLC is available at this airport.

#### VFR

Louisville International airport is surrounded by class C airspace. Aircraft entering class C airspace VFR require a clearance in accordance 
with [7110.65 Chapter 7, section 9-2](https://www.faa.gov/air_traffic/publications/atpubs/atc_html/chap7_section_8.html).

**VFR Deaprture:**  
Cleared out of the Louisville class charlie airspace to the west, maintain VFR at or below 2500 until further advised. Departure frequency 122.8. Squawk 0301.

**VFR Local Pattern Example:**  
Cleared into the bravo, join left downwind runway 17L, report midfield with intentions.

**VFR squawk code assignment:**  
via Aurora

